reviews.author: Michelle
reviews.text: Temples are supposed to be a place of solice and openness, but after going quite far out of my way to seek this on a day I really needed to feel the presence of something larger than myself in order to seek my answers, ask for forgiveness, and release heavy burdens, I was denied access. To make matters worse, the teenage girls attending the entrance were rude; they giggled upon delivering news that since I was not a member with identification, I could not visit for one session. Laughing at not being inclusive is a sign of mockery and helps maintain the image that religion is "bad" through segregation. I hope the Church reads this review in order to help raise the next generation. This is not an acceptable behavior. PS. Even though I was denied inside access, I was still allowed to walk the grounds and visit the exterior sights of the gardens to accomplish two of the three intentions sought that day. Hence, two stars.
